<section class="border-y border-border bg-gradient-to-b from-surface to-transparent py-32 max-md:py-20" id="problem">
  <div class="layout-wrap">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 items-start gap-12 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-20">
      <div class="fi opacity-0 translate-y-[18px] transition-[opacity,transform] duration-[650ms] ease-out [&.in]:translate-y-0 [&.in]:opacity-100">
        <div class="mb-3.5 text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-text-kicker before:text-[rgba(139,124,255,0.62)] before:content-['//_']">The problem</div>
        <h2 class="mb-5 font-display text-[clamp(30px,3.5vw,50px)] font-bold leading-[1.02] tracking-[-0.06em]">One mind.<br><em class="not-italic text-accent">Five separate apps.</em></h2>
        <p class="max-w-[520px] text-sm leading-[1.75] text-text-dim">
          Every AI tool has its own way of learning about you. 
          You end up repeating your instructions, brand voice, and project context in five different places—and they drift apart the moment you update one.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="fi flex flex-col delay-100 opacity-0 translate-y-[18px] transition-[opacity,transform] duration-[650ms] ease-out [&.in]:translate-y-0 [&.in]:opacity-100 [&>div:last-child]:border-b-0">
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-[18px] border-b border-border py-[22px]">
          <div class="w-5 shrink-0 text-[10px] text-text-faint">01</div>
          <div class="text-[13px] leading-[1.65] text-text-dim [&_code]:text-[12px] [&_code]:text-[rgba(139,124,255,0.62)] [&_strong]:font-normal [&_strong]:text-text">
            <strong>Claude</strong> needs your custom instructions in its own specific settings.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-[18px] border-b border-border py-[22px]">
          <div class="w-5 shrink-0 text-[10px] text-text-faint">02</div>
          <div class="text-[13px] leading-[1.65] text-text-dim [&_code]:text-[12px] [&_code]:text-[rgba(139,124,255,0.62)] [&_strong]:font-normal [&_strong]:text-text">
            <strong>ChatGPT or Gemini</strong> requires you to copy-paste the same context over and over.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-[18px] border-b border-border py-[22px]">
          <div class="w-5 shrink-0 text-[10px] text-text-faint">03</div>
          <div class="text-[13px] leading-[1.65] text-text-dim [&_code]:text-[12px] [&_code]:text-[rgba(139,124,255,0.62)] [&_strong]:font-normal [&_strong]:text-text">
            <strong>Cursor, Windsurf, Trae, Kiro, Mistral Vibe, Antigravity</strong> — each tool expects instructions in a different hidden folder.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-[18px] border-b border-border py-[22px]">
          <div class="w-5 shrink-0 text-[10px] text-text-faint">04</div>
          <div class="text-[13px] leading-[1.65] text-text-dim [&_strong]:font-normal [&_strong]:text-text">
